As mixed reactions trail the death of a Christian female student Deborah Yakubu, for alleged blasphemy against Prophet Mohammed the Imam of National Mosque Abuja, Ibrahim Maqari, has said Muslims have some red lines which must not be crossed especially as regards the dignity of the Prophet. According to him, if grievances are not properly addressed no one should be criticized for addressing them individually. A statement posted on the Imam’s Twitter account read, “It should be known to everyone that we the Muslims have some red lines beyond which MUST NOT be crossed. The dignity of the Prophet (PBUH) is at the forefront of the red lines. -Advertisement- “If our grievances are not properly addressed, then you should not be criticized for addressing them ourselves.”